NOTE:  Under WI State Statute 6.03(1)(b) a person found guilty of a felony that you are ineligible to vote in any election until your civil rights are restored!

Def to enroll in the Ashland County Adult Drug Court & complete successfully.  Def to advise drug ct coordinator of all prescriptions currently taking & when they are filled.
  Defendant shall not possess or consume alcoholic beverages, illegal drugs, or any mind altering substances (MAS).  MAS means alcoholic beverages, controlled substances other than those prescribed by treating physician to the Defendant, inhalants, synthetic marijuana or a similar substance, and/or over-the-counter medications used contrary to label instructions.  THE DEFENDANT IS TO MAINTAIN ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
The Defendant shall not enter any bars, taverns, liquor stores (any place where the primary purpose is the sale of alcohol) where mind altering substances are present, consumed or sold..NO possession of meth paraphernalia.
  The Def is to take all medications as prescribed by treating physician and only in the manner & dosage as prescribed!
  The Def is subject to random UA testing.
Def to have NO contact w/any known methamphetamine users or dealers except for as associated with drug ct or treatment.  Known meth users/dealers means people that have been charged with/or convicted of meth offenses or that the def personally knows to be users/dealers of meth.
  The Def is to obtain counseling as directed by DOC at the expense of the Def.
  The Def is to provide a DNA specimen.
Undergo inpatient treatment prior to entry into drug ct/completed.
To seek, obtain and maintain half time employment.
Restitution is set at -0-.  If during the period of supervision, a claim for restitution is made the Def will be notified!
